From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Serialize gen_proto invocations to avoid parallel race

gen_proto.py both writes the .proto/.proto3 files and runs protoc on
them to produce Python pb3 code. onnx-data.in.proto's generated
onnx-data.proto3 imports onnx/onnx-ml.proto3, which is produced by the
gen_proto.py invocation for onnx.in.proto. The two custom commands only
declared their .in.proto file as a dependency, so with a parallel build
(ninja -j N) the onnx-data invocation could race ahead and fail with:

    onnx/onnx-ml.proto3: File not found.
    "TensorProto" is not defined.

Make each gen_proto.py custom command also depend on the proto files
generated by previous iterations of the foreach loop so the invocations
are serialized in dependency order.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
 CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -399,7 +399,7 @@
     # Use add_custom_command to avoid re-generate of PROTO files
     add_custom_command(OUTPUT "${GENERATED_PROTO}"
         COMMAND ${ONNX_PYTHON_INTERPRETER} "${GEN_PROTO_PY}" ${GEN_PROTO_ARGS}
-        DEPENDS ${INFILE}
+        DEPENDS ${INFILE} ${GENERATED_FILES}
         COMMENT "Running gen_proto.py on ${INFILE}")
     message("Generated: ${GENERATED_PROTO}")

